"SendFilesDescription" = "To send a file to your Android device, click on the Share icon or right-click on the file and select \"Share\". Afterward, select \"QuickDrop\" from the list of apps and follow the instructions.

If you don't see QuickDrop in the list, click on \"Edit Extensions\", scroll down, and enable the toggle for QuickDrop.

You also can send the current content of your Mac's clipboard to your Android device by clicking on QuickDrop's menu bar icon and selecting \"Send Clipboard\".";

"UserManualDescription" = "When QuickDrop is running, it will appear in the menu bar at the top of your screen. Click the QuickDrop icon if you would like to stop receiving files.
            
To send files from your Android device to your Mac, tap on the share icon on your phone, and select \"Quick Share\". Your Mac will be listed as an available device. Files will be saved in your Downloads folder.

Important: Your Android device and your Mac need to be on the same WiFi network to transfer files.";

"TroubleshootingDescription" = "If your Mac does not show up on your Android device or the transmission failed, try the following:

1) Make sure that both devices are connected to the same WiFi network. Note: Guest networks usually do not allow devices to communicate with each other. If you are on a guest network, please switch to your home network.

2) Open System Settings, and go to \"Privacy & Security\" > \"Local Network\". Make sure that QuickDrop is enabled. If you use a third-party firewall or an antivirus program, please check the documentation of this program to allow incoming connections for QuickDrop.

3) Restart QuickDrop by clicking the menu bar icon, choose the last entry, and open the app again. Restart your Android device.

If you still encounter issues, try to use the separate QuickDrop app for your smartphone. For more information, please check the \"Mobile App\" section on the left.";


